  "text": "A similar argument can be made for ON-type velocity-sensitive DINs. The dense distribution of these DINs in the coding-space and the possibility to model them well by shifting a single parameter suggests that only few individual DINs belong to this DIN cluster. In fact, physiological data suggest that only two individual DINs with very similar properties belong to this cluster. The two DINs mainly differ in that one responds to the ipsi-, and the other to the contralateral antenna [CITATION_1] .",
